\title{Jacobian - Isometric Log Ratio Transform}
\tag{private}
\author{meenaljhajharia}
\texpackage{preamble}
\import{basic-macros}

\p{Given a density #{p_X(x)} defined over simplices #{x \in \simplex{N-1}},
we can transform it to a density over unconstrained parameters #{y \in
\R^{N-1}} by applying the inverse ILR transformation and adjusting
for the change of variables, which yields
##{
  p_Y(y) = p_X(\textrm{ilr}^{-1}(y)) \absdet{\jac_{s}(y)},
}}